{
  "title": "weather genie",
  "description": "This space provides sample AccuWeather datasets containing daily and day/night historical weather metrics for the top 50 global cities, supporting business analysis and data exploration of weather\u2019s impact.\n\n**Capabilities:**\n- Analyze and compare key weather parameters such as temperature, precipitation, humidity, and wind across global cities and over time.\n- Identify regional and temporal patterns, outliers, and correlations in historical weather data using both metric and imperial units.\n- Support business questions around economic risk analysis, energy demand forecasting, supply chain impacts, consumer behavior, and weather-driven sales or advertising strategies.\n- Visualize weather trends using time series, heatmaps, or box plots to understand variability and extreme events.\n\n**Limitations:**\n- Data is limited to a one-month sample and a reduced set of attributes, intended for exploration rather than production.\n- Full historical depth, complete data attributes, and broader city coverage require access to the complete AccuWeather Data Suite on the [Databricks Marketplace](https://databricks.com/marketplace/consumer/listings/235b45d2-d625-4c1c-90a2-68e4568dda40).\n- Not suitable for precise forecasting, real-time decision-making, or applications requiring complete climatic records.",
